  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a 10-year sentence requested by a disruptive spectator is disproportionate to the scale of the crime and the defendant's lack of prior record. A custodial sentence of 6 months is sufficient to serve as a deterrent and punishment while allowing for rehabilitation, taking into account the mitigating factors of the plea and restitution efforts.",
  "verdict": 6
}
